properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued March 3 at 3:46AM AKST until March 5 at 4:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northeast winds 35 to 55 mph with gusts of 70 to 80 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Thompson Pass to Valdez city.

* WHEN...From late Wednesday afternoon through Thursday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...High winds could move loose debris, damage property,
and cause power outages. Travel could be difficult, especially
for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds will increase across the zone
through Wednesday with warning level wind potential from Thompson Pass to
Valdez proper by late Wednesday afternoon. Areas of blowing snow
will likely continue.
properties.instruction:
A high wind watch means there is potential for a hazardous high
wind event. Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates
on this situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a
safe location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM LATE WEDNESDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH THURSDAY AFTERNOON
